dcterms:description: A toy problem designed to study the properties of CNN feature maps in deep reinforcement learning, where a ball falls from the top of the screen and the agent controls a paddle to catch it.
dcterms:title: Catch

dcterms:description: A modified version of the Catch dataset that includes background noise, making it more challenging for deep reinforcement learning methods without visual attention.
dcterms:title: Catch with Background (CatchBG)

dcterms:description: A set of classic video games used for experiments in deep reinforcement learning, specifically mentioned games include Breakout, Seaquest, MsPacman, and Centipede.
dcterms:title: Atari Games
